Solving in a Second
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b White to play\b0 .
\par It is easy, but there is only one winning move.
\par
\par If White is too careless he might ends up in shortage of liberties, but being too calm can put him in trouble as well.
\par
\par The first move is the vital point.
\par
\par
\par }
